This is where you describe your class. Do a general description of what the class is for. Then follow it with your name as the author of the class. (If it is a pair project, do both names.) You do the author with the @author structure below. Note that if you know html tags, you can add some of them into your javadoc. For example, you could use bold to make bold type or italic or bold and italic or use the paragraph code

...

to surround a paragraph. Get ahold of an html manual if you want to go crazy with this.

You can also do bullet lists:
  • first item
  • second item which goes across lines
or numbered lists:
  1. first numbered item
  2. second numbered item
  3. third numbered item
or pictures:

or references to other sites:

Plotting applet
